        <TD bgcolor='black' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana' size='2'> Cazel can still be soloed, but it took me approximately 25 minutes.</P><P>- We are talking level 60, epic equipped, max summon, focused, buffed spectre pet (at least for the first 15 minutes on the buffed part)</P><P>- We're also talking using only the most efficient DoTs and the pet.</P><P>- We're finally, and most importantly, talking about a good spot for fear kiting pathing that allows you to med and fear without chasing.  </P><P>Since fear pathing as bad as that is almost an exploit (although I do not believe it is, he's real close to you when it does break, it's definitely not without risk), I don't recommend it.  </P><P>I also learned of this fear pathing spot by watching another Warlock try it with Cazel... and die.  So it's not without risk.  I believe I droppped below one bubble of health 2-3 times during the fight from lich or a bad fear break.  After 10-15 minutes, your pet is high enough up on the aggro list that fear breaks get a little safer, then you just need to watch your pet's health and switch a DoT to a pact and use a few more vexxings.</P><P>I did not have any other sources of manaless damage than the epic, so it could conceivably get a bit easier than I had it with those sources, but you need to keep Epic DoT, plus max hitting spec, plus at least one other DoT on him to make his HP drop.</P><P>Remember that fear kiting gives almost 100% of the time at full DoT damage on Cazel (he doesn't even run to you when fear breaks, he just summons).  While regular kiting you're only getting 66% of the DoT damage because of the kiting rules.  This means fear kiting is definitely the way to go.</P><P><BR>Therros Rex'Necri<BR>Tier'Dal Warlock<BR>Tarew Marr</font></td>
